&lt;p&gt;LOCUM CONSULTANT - PAEDIATRIC DENTISTRY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FIXED TERM CONTRACT - 12 MONTHS - FULL TIME (10 PA&#39;S)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust Community Dental Services seeks to recruit a locum Specialist / Consultant in Paediatric Dentistry to support service delivery across North Yorkshire and York. The post holder will be responsible for delivery of high quality level 3 services, as well as supporting the service in delivery of level 2 Paediatric Dentistry within a Community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Subject to negotiation, clinical sessions may be delivered in York, Scarborough, Harrogate and Northallerton supporting our team of Specialists in Paediatric dentistry, Senior Dental Officers and Dental Therapists. This highly equipped team have access to digital radiography, operating microscope, computer based records and is well integrated with both Harrogate and York acute hospital systems. In addition, treatment under conscious sedation is available in all areas and treatment sessions under general anaesthesia are delivered at 3 acute sites across the service in Northallerton, York and Harrogate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Caroline Graham on 01423 542323. Further enquiries can be made to the Service Manager, Lesley Horton on 01423 557404. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caroline Graham, Consultant in Special Care Dentistry / Clinical Lead at caroline.graham3@nhs.net or call 07798857531&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:  Lesley Horton, Service Manager l.horton2@nhs.net or call 07741700486.&lt;/p&gt;
